Requirements:

AWC CLI installed on the host and AWS credentials configured for more informaiton  http://aws.amazon.com/cli/
Python 3.x preferably 3.8

Limitations:

The this scipt uses the defaul AWS CLI profile.

Installation:

Create a directory in your home directory called cost-calculator
Change to that directory then execute the following steps
Copy or clone the content to the newly created directory

tar -zxvf cost-calcualtor.tar.gz
python3.8 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -r requirements.txt

How to run it:

python ./cost-calculator.py --region us-east-1 --cluster inmemorycluster <--day-range 1> <--output hourly_cost_estimate.scv>

parameters:
--region AWS region name
--cluster ElastiCache cluster name
optional parameters: 
--day-range: default value of 1 i.e. for the past 24 hours one calculation per hour. 
--output: CSV file name, default value cost_estimate_cluster_name_"%H:%M_%d_%m_%Y".csv
